<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:lang="en" xml:id="xlread_scan">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>xlread_scan</refname>
        <refpurpose>Auxiliary function used by xlread</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
          [value,text] = xlread_scan(data,isText,isNum,tightFlag)
        </synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
                <term>data,isText,isNum</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>These parameters are described as the outputs of <link linkend="xlread_data">xlread_data</link>.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                  <term>tightFlag</term>
                  <listitem>
                      <para>a boolean. If <term>tightFlag</term> is true, then the <term>value,text</term> matrices tightly enclose the region where data of the corresponding type is found. This is the case when the <term>range</term> is not specified in the <term>xlread</term> call.
                      </para>
                  </listitem>
              </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>text</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>a matrix of strings containing the textual data found in the sheet at specfied range.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>value</term>
              <listitem>
                  <para>a matrix of numbers containing the numerical data found in the sheet at specfied range.
                  </para>
              </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
 This low level function is called by the main <term>xlread</term> function (see the dedicated <link linkend="xlread">help page</link>) but it can be used after calling <term>xlread_data</term> and some subsequent raw data processing.
</para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection role="see also">
        <title>See also</title>
        <simplelist type="inline">
          <member>
              <link linkend="xlread">xlread</link>
          </member>
          <member>
              <link linkend="xlread_data">xlread_data</link>
          </member>
          <member>
              <link linkend="xlwrite">xlwrite</link>
          </member>
          <member>
              <link linkend="xlinfo">xlinfo</link>
          </member>
        </simplelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Bibliography</title>
        <para>This function is based on POI library (<ulink url="http://poi.apache.org/">http://poi.apache.org/</ulink>).
        </para>
    </refsection>
</refentry>

